Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). In a large bowl, combine butter, confectioners' sugar, egg, almond extract and vanilla extract. beat until smooth. Mix in flour and salt. Roll into 4 inch strips, place on baking sheet. Curve top down to form handle of cane. Bake in preheated oven for 9 to 10 minutes. While still warm, remove from pan and sprinkle with candy and sugar mixture.